@startuml
' Sequence diagram for the UDP Chinese proverb example.
' Focus: ChineseProverbClient <-> ChineseProverbServer workflow over
' connectionless UDP. There is no accept, no boss/worker split, no codec
' stack, and no handshake — each DatagramPacket carries its own src/dst.
'
' Render with a PlantUML IDE plugin, the PlantUML CLI, or
' https://www.plantuml.com/plantuml/uml/.

title UDP Round-Trip: ChineseProverbClient <-> ChineseProverbServer (broadcast)

skinparam maxMessageSize 0
skinparam BoxPadding 6
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
autonumber

actor "Client\nmain" as CMain
box "ChineseProverbClient\n(NioDatagramChannel, bound to ephemeral port)" #E7F3FF
    participant "ChineseProverbClient" as Client
    participant "ChineseProverbClientHandler\nSimpleChannelInboundHandler<DatagramPacket>" as CH
end box

box "Network (UDP broadcast 255.255.255.255:8080)" #F5F5F5
    participant "Datagram\n(socket)" as Net
end box

box "ChineseProverbServer\n(NioDatagramChannel, bound to :8080)" #E8F5E9
    participant "ChineseProverbServerHandler\nSimpleChannelInboundHandler<DatagramPacket>" as SH
    participant "ChineseProverbServer" as Server
end box
actor "Server\nmain" as SMain

== 1. Server bootstrap (connectionless — no accept, no boss/worker) ==

SMain -> Server : run(port)
activate Server #B5E5C1
Server -> Server : group =\n  MultiThreadIoEventLoopGroup(NioIoHandler.newFactory())\n  Bootstrap.channel(NioDatagramChannel)\n  .option(SO_BROADCAST, true)
note right of Server
  UDP server pipeline (addLast order):
    1. handler : ChineseProverbServerHandler  (inbound, DatagramPacket)
  No codecs, no frame decoders — datagrams are self-delimiting.
  A single EventLoopGroup handles both I/O and business logic;
  NioDatagramChannel has no ServerSocketChannel counterpart
  because UDP has no accept() step.
end note
Server -> Net : bind(InetSocketAddress(port)).syncUninterruptibly()
Net --> Server : bound; channel bound to UDP :8080\n  closeFuture.awaitUninterruptibly() blocks
deactivate Server

== 2. Client bootstrap (bind ephemeral port to receive replies) ==

CMain -> Client : run(port)
activate Client #A6D8F0
Client -> Client : group =\n  MultiThreadIoEventLoopGroup(NioIoHandler.newFactory())\n  Bootstrap.channel(NioDatagramChannel)\n  .option(SO_BROADCAST, true)
note right of Client
  UDP client pipeline (addLast order):
    1. handler : ChineseProverbClientHandler  (inbound, DatagramPacket)
  Client is also connectionless: bind(0) asks the OS for an
  ephemeral port so the server has an address to reply to.
  No connect() — writeAndFlush supplies the destination per packet.
end note
Client -> Net : bind(0).syncUninterruptibly()  // OS assigns ephemeral port
Net --> Client : channel active on ephemeral port P
deactivate Client

== 3. Client -> Server : broadcast query (single packet, no handshake) ==

Client -> Client : new DatagramPacket(\n  Unpooled.copiedBuffer("Proverb dictionary query?", UTF_8),\n  new InetSocketAddress("255.255.255.255", port))
Client -> Net : writeAndFlush(datagramPacket).syncUninterruptibly()\n  // destination = broadcast 255.255.255.255 : 8080
Net -> Net : UDP broadcast delivered to every host\n  on the subnet whose socket is bound to :8080
Net -> SH : DatagramPacket\n  content = "Proverb dictionary query?"\n  sender = client ephemeral (hostIP:P)

== 4. Server receives and replies ==

activate SH
SH -> SH : channelRead0(ctx, packet)\n  req = packet.content().toString(UTF_8)\n  log.info("{}", req)
alt !"Proverb dictionary query?".equals(req)
    SH -> SH : return  // silently drop\n  no reply sent, no NACK (UDP)
else req == "Proverb dictionary query?"
    SH -> SH : nextQuote()\n  quoteId = ThreadLocalRandom.current().nextInt(DICTIONARY.length)\n  return DICTIONARY[quoteId]
    SH -> SH : new DatagramPacket(\n    Unpooled.copiedBuffer("Proverb query result: " + quote, UTF_8),\n    packet.sender())  // reply addressed to client's (hostIP:P)
    SH -> Net : ctx.writeAndFlush(replyDatagram)\n  // unicast back to sender, not broadcast
end
deactivate SH

== 5. Client receives reply and closes ==

Net -> CH : DatagramPacket\n  content = "Proverb query result: <quote>"\n  sender = server (hostIP:8080)
activate CH
CH -> CH : channelRead0(ctx, packet)\n  response = packet.content().toString(UTF_8)
alt !response.startsWith("Proverb query result: ")
    CH -> CH : ignore  // not our reply (broadcasts may carry other traffic)
else response.startsWith("Proverb query result: ")
    CH -> CH : log.info("{}", response)
    CH -> CH : ctx.close()  // triggers client channel closeFuture
end
deactivate CH
Client -> Net : channel closed
Net --> Client : closeFuture returns\n  // awaitUninterruptibly(15000) returns true (no timeout)
Client -> Net : finally: group.shutdownGracefully().syncUninterruptibly()
Server -> Net : finally: group.shutdownGracefully().syncUninterruptibly()  // on Ctrl-C / SIGINT

== 6. Timeout path (no reply within 15 s) ==

note over Client #FFF3E0
  If no matching reply arrives within 15 s
  (packet lost, server down, or wrong subnet):
    ch.closeFuture().awaitUninterruptibly(15000) returns false
    -> log.info("Query TimeOut.")
    -> finally: group.shutdownGracefully().syncUninterruptibly()
  Note: UDP gives no delivery guarantee. A lost query or lost reply
  is indistinguishable from a slow one without application-level
  retries or sequence numbers.
end note

== 7. Exception paths ==

note over SH #FFE0E0
  ChineseProverbServerHandler.exceptionCaught(ctx, cause):
    log.info("channel exception", cause);
    ctx.close();
  Closes the datagram channel — the server stops receiving on :8080.
end note

note over CH #FFE0E0
  ChineseProverbClientHandler.exceptionCaught(ctx, cause):
    log.error("channel exception", cause);
    ctx.close();
  Closes the client channel — closeFuture returns,
  awaitUninterruptibly(15000) unblocks immediately.
end note

@enduml
